      ]
    },
    { "typ": "resources",
      "cre": "2016-02-28T09:14:26",
      "mod": "2016-02-28T09:14:26",
      "uuid": "290df075"
    },
    { "typ": "textblock",
      "cre": "2016-02-28T09:16:38",
      "mod": "2016-02-28T09:17:14",
      "h": 73.498,
      "ind": 0,
      "sheet": 0,
      "split": [ ],
      "uuid": "8ffc8d29",
      "y0": 72.0,
      "cc": [
        { "typ": "text",
          "cre": "2016-02-28T09:16:38",
          "mod": "2016-02-28T09:17:14",
          "lines": [
            0,
            62,
            119
          ],
          "text": "I have set Ctrl-X to mark a version as “Rejected.” I think it would be nice to automatically purge whenever photohoard exits normally.",
          "uuid": "4a8102cc"
        }
      ]
    },
    { "typ": "textblock",
      "cre": "2016-02-28T09:17:31",
      "mod": "2016-02-28T09:19:04",
      "h": 73.498,
      "ind": 1,
      "sheet": 0,
      "split": [ ],
      "uuid": "888cb92d",
      "y0": 145.498,
      "cc": [
        { "typ": "text",
          "cre": "2016-02-28T09:17:31",
          "mod": "2016-02-28T09:19:04",
          "lines": [
            0,
            57,
            118
          ],
          "text": "At the very least, rejected versions of a photo that has other versions associated with it can simply be deleted, and their cache entries dropped.",
          "uuid": "7825d31c"
        }
      ]
    },
    { "typ": "textblock",
      "cre": "2016-02-28T09:18:18",
      "mod": "2016-02-28T09:20:08",
      "h": 119.83,
      "ind": 1,
      "sheet": 0,
      "split": [ ],
      "uuid": "8062ef4d",
      "y0": 218.996,
      "cc": [
        { "typ": "text",
          "cre": "2016-02-28T09:18:18",
          "mod": "2016-02-28T09:20:08",
          "lines": [
            0,
            55,
            112,
            176,
            238
          ],
          "text": "Rejected versions that are the only version of a photo should be treated with some care. Simply deleting such a version would leave an image file on disk that will never again be loaded, because Scanner will ignore it, since the photo is already in the db. I think that may not be desirable.",
          "uuid": "757f9aa2",
          "cc": [
            { "typ": "markup",
              "cre": "2016-02-28T09:18:34",
              "mod": "2016-02-28T09:18:34",
              "end": 35,
              "start": 31,
              "style": 1,
              "uuid": "ec512fd5"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    { "typ": "textblock",
      "cre": "2016-02-28T09:20:26",
      "mod": "2016-02-28T09:21:11",
      "h": 73.498,
      "ind": 1,
      "sheet": 0,
      "split": [ ],
      "uuid": "54b86417",
      "y0": 338.826,
      "cc": [
        { "typ": "text",
          "cre": "2016-02-28T09:20:26",
          "mod": "2016-02-28T09:21:11",
          "lines": [
            0,
            60,
            117
          ],
          "text": "Deleting the version along with its photo is not an option, because then the beast would simply pop up next time the folder tree is scanned.",
          "uuid": "55fc94cd"
        }
      ]
    },
    { "typ": "textblock",
      "cre": "2016-02-28T09:21:12",
      "mod": "2016-02-28T09:21:41",
      "h": 73.498,
      "ind": 1,
      "sheet": 0,
      "split": [ ],
      "uuid": "c8c830d0",
      "y0": 412.324,
      "cc": [
        { "typ": "text",
          "cre": "2016-02-28T09:21:12",
          "mod": "2016-02-28T09:21:41",
          "lines": [
            0,
            62,
            123
          ],
          "text": "Deleting the image file is an option, but that should only be done with user confirmation. And probably only upon explicit user request.",
          "uuid": "99d2a573",
          "cc": [
            { "typ": "markup",
              "cre": "2016-02-28T09:21:20",
              "mod": "2016-02-28T09:21:20",
              "end": 26,
              "start": 24,
              "style": 1,
              "uuid": "4108482b"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    { "typ": "textblock",
      "cre": "2016-02-28T09:21:54",
      "mod": "2016-02-28T09:27:14",
      "h": 189.328,
      "ind": 1,
      "sheet": 0,
      "split": [ ],
      "uuid": "6c0898cc",
      "y0": 485.822,
      "cc": [
        { "typ": "text",
          "cre": "2016-02-28T09:21:54",
          "mod": "2016-02-28T09:27:14",
          "lines": [
            0,
            62,
            126,
            187,
            241,
            301,
            365,
            422
          ],
          "text": "So perhaps, the right thing to do is to leave purging manual? Ctrl-Shift-X could trigger it. A dialog would pop up that says: “About to purge n versions of m photos.” (If m = n, it would simply ask “About to purge m photos.” It would have a checkbox that says “Delete rejected image files.” A balloon help to this checkbox would say: “Checking this box will delete k image files from your hard disk and move them into the system Trash.” ",
          "uuid": "2d40babf",
          "cc": [
            { "typ": "markup",
              "cre": "2016-02-28T09:22:47",
              "mod": "2016-02-28T09:22:47",
              "end": 143,
              "start": 142,
              "style": 1,
              "uuid": "9807ae33"
            },
            { "typ": "markup",
              "cre": "2016-02-28T09:23:11",
