    { "typ": "textblock",
      "cre": "2016-02-28T09:27:30",
      "mod": "2016-02-28T09:29:06",
      "h": 119.83,
      "ind": 1,
      "sheet": 1,
      "split": [ ],
      "uuid": "6cc4cee3",
      "y0": 99.166,
      "cc": [
        { "typ": "text",
          "cre": "2016-02-28T09:27:30",
          "mod": "2016-02-28T09:29:06",
          "lines": [
            0,
            56,
            121,
            186,
            249
          ],
          "text": "Note how complicated this all is: Let’s say there are 5 versions of photo A, 3 of which are rejects; 2 versions of photo B, both of which are rejects; and 1 version of photo C, which is a reject. Then there would be 6 versions of 3 photos rejected, but only 2 image files are subject to deletion.",
          "uuid": "db2fc6df"
        }
      ]
    },
    { "typ": "textblock",
      "cre": "2016-02-28T09:29:25",
